      "title": "Division of Powers (Federal vs Provincial)",
      "coreDefinition": "Legislative powers are divided between federal and provincial governments under sections 91 and 92 of the Constitution Act, 1867.",
      "frameworkSteps": [
        "Identify the subject matter of legislation.",
        "Classify under federal or provincial head of power.",
        "Apply pith and substance analysis if necessary."
      ],
      "quickExamples": [
