      "id": "lcc_section_1_oakes",
      "title": "Section 1 and the Oakes Test",
      "coreDefinition": "Even if a Charter right is infringed, the government may justify the limitation under Section 1 if it is reasonable and demonstrably justified in a free and democratic society.",
      "frameworkSteps": [
        "Identify pressing and substantial objective.",
        "Establish rational connection.",
        "Demonstrate minimal impairment.",
        "Assess proportionality of effects."
      ],
      "quickExamples": [
        "Limits on speech may be upheld if proportional and narrowly tailored."
      ],
      "commonMistakes": [
        "Assuming any infringement is automatically invalid.",
        "Ignoring proportionality analysis."
      ],
